onicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Childrens-party.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Childrens-party.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Childrens-party-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa hosted the Children’s Party at State House in Bulawayo ahead of today’s main celebrations The Children’s Party held at State House in yesterday ran under the same theme. President Mnangagwa hosted the Children’s Party at State House in Bulawayo ahead of today’s main celebrations. Also yesterday, the Independence Flame and Independence Trophy were taken on a seven-hour tour of Bulawayo’s western suburbs. <img class="size-full wp-image-600985" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-of-the-flame-.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-of-the-flame-.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-of-the-flame--360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Independence Flame touring Bulawayo suburbs From Saturday, The Independence Flame was resting at Khami National Monument and was  guarded by members of the police overnight. In the morning a convoy of security details took the flame from the top of the King’s enclosure at the Khami National Monument, mounted it on the back of a truck, then it was taken to koBullet in Nketa. <img class="size-full wp-image-600984" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Uhuru-Flame-at-Joshua-Nkomos-statue.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Uhuru-Flame-at-Joshua-Nkomos-statue.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Uhuru-Flame-at-Joshua-Nkomos-statue-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Uhuru Flame at the Joshua Nkomo statue There, Government officials such as Minister Ncube welcomed it, with Zimbabwe football giants, Highlanders and Dynamos supporters, officials and players and residents waiting for the Independence Flame. The two teams then joined the convoy, as a way to hype their match today at Barbourfields Stadium as they play for the Independence Trophy. Highlanders FC captain Ariel Sibanda and his Dynamos counterpart Partson Jaure were at the back of a pick-up parading the Independence Trophy. <img class="size-full wp-image-600982" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Bosso-captains-.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Bosso-captains-.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Bosso-captains--360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Highlanders FC captain Ariel Sibanda and his Dynamos counterpart Partson Jaure At midnight there was a fireworks display at the Tower Block Municipal. <img class="size-full wp-image-600979" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/fireworks-.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/fireworks-.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/fireworks--360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Fireworks lit up the Bulawayo night sky at midnight Join us for live updates from Barbourfields Stadium.